  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> and <strong>Chantenay carrots</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim and finely chop the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Dissolve <strong>half </strong>the<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> (save the rest for later!) in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped spring onion</strong>, <strong>dried sage</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>chicken stock</strong> and stir it all together, then set aside to absorb – this is your <strong>stuffing mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-2--spring-o-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-2--spring-o-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-2--spring-o-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-2--spring-o-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-2--spring-o-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>stuffing mixture</strong> into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> <strong>stuffing balls</strong> and add them to a baking tray with the<strong> chicken breast portions</strong></p><p>Drizzle the chicken with <strong>olive oil</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2005.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, heat a small pan with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs, stirring to form a paste</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>remaining chicken stock mix </strong>in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and add to the pan with the <strong>Marmite</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
